1. Navigate to /home/ubuntu/CAPS/Testing_final

    cd /home/ubuntu/CAPS/Testing_final

2. Navigate to the backend container and randomize first the answer

    docker exec -it caps_backend bash

    (NOTE: SKIP THIS PART IN PRODUCTION!!): php artisan choices:randomize-correct 


3. Type this command:

    php artisan migrate

    php artisan migrate --path=Modules/Users/Database/Migrations/2025_06_21_000002_create_student_remarks_table.php

    php artisan migrate --path=Modules/Users/Database/Migrations/2025_06_22_000001_create_student_curricula_table.php

    php artisan migrate --path=Modules/PracticeExams/Database/Migrations/2025_06_22_000002_create_personal_exam_settings_table.php

    php artisan migrate --path=Modules/Users/Database/Migrations/2025_06_22_000003_create_student_teacher_enrollments_table.php 

    php artisan migrate --path=Modules/PracticeExams/Database/Migrations/2025_06_22_000004_create_personal_practice_exam_results_table.php

It will migrate the table named:

- remarks
- curriculum
- student_grades
- student_curricula
- personal_exam_setting
- student_teacher_enrollments
- student_remarks
- personal_practice_exam_result
- practice_exam_drafts_table

Another field will be added in the subjects table named:
- is_enabled_for_exam_questions

4. Seed the database for the new migrations:
    php artisan db:seed

5. It should show errors only in the users table:

 - Duplicate Data (Due to test accounts.) This error is acceptable


6. After running the commands above, run this specific command 

- php artisan student-grades:import
- php artisan students:sync-curricula
- php artisan students:assign-remarks